         <div type="translation">
            <p>To king  Melek-[yathon]</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Transcription from Myres. Similar fragmentary bowls found at the temple enable
                    restoring the entire formula (see NY.NY.MMA.P.2275-95): "On the nineteenth day
                    of the month... in the year IV of the king Melek-yathon, king of Cithion and
                    Idalion, Ebed-Melqarth son of Ebed-Adoni vowed an image/this gift which he gave
                    to his lord Eshmnun-Melqarth. May he bless" (Myres, 302). </p>
         </div>
